# HTML/Svelte Formatting Rules

## **NEVER Use Dangling Closing Brackets**

**CRITICAL**: Never place closing `>` brackets on their own line in HTML or Svelte markup. Always keep the closing `>` on the same line as the last attribute.

### ❌ DON'T: Dangling closing bracket
```svelte
<div
	class="container"
	style="min-height: {innerHeight}px;"
>
	Content here
</div>

<button
	type="submit"
	class="btn btn-primary"
	onclick={handleClick}
>
	Click me
</button>
```

### ✅ DO: Keep closing bracket with last attribute
```svelte
<div
	class="container"
	style="min-height: {innerHeight}px;">
	Content here
</div>

<button
	type="submit"
	class="btn btn-primary"
	onclick={handleClick}>
	Click me
</button>
```

### ✅ DO: Single line when possible
```svelte
<div class="container" style="min-height: {innerHeight}px;">Content</div>
<button type="submit" class="btn" onclick={handleClick}>Click me</button>
```

## **Self-Closing Tags Follow Same Rule**

### ❌ DON'T: Dangling self-closing bracket
```svelte
<input
	type="text"
	class="form-input"
	placeholder="Enter text"
/>

<img
	src="/image.jpg"
	alt="Description"
	class="w-full h-auto"
/>
```

### ✅ DO: Keep self-closing bracket with last attribute
```svelte
<input
	type="text"
	class="form-input"
	placeholder="Enter text" />

<img
	src="/image.jpg"
	alt="Description"
	class="w-full h-auto" />
```

## **Applies to All HTML Elements**

This rule applies to:
- Regular HTML elements (`<div>`, `<button>`, `<span>`, etc.)
- Svelte components (`<MyComponent>`)
- Self-closing elements (`<input />`, `<img />`, `<br />`)
- Elements with many attributes
- Elements with Svelte directives and bindings

## **Reasoning**

- **Consistency**: Maintains uniform bracket placement across the codebase
- **Readability**: Keeps related syntax together on the same line
- **Editor Support**: Works better with most code formatters and linters
- **Prevents Visual Noise**: Reduces unnecessary line breaks that don't add meaning